								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="264" ruledLines="42" writtenLines="42">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and stitching. </p>
									<p>264 columns in total, three to six columns per membrane. </p>
									<p>Three tagin on שעטנזגץ, and one on אבדהיח. </p>
									<p>The letter ח arched throughout. </p>
									<p>Several instances of majuscular and minuscular letters. </p>
									<p>Special shapes of the letter  ו, נ, פ, ע, ח, ז, י, ל, ס, ר occur. The inverted נ before and after Num. 10:35-36. </p>
									<p>The &quot;puncta extraordinaria&quot; placed on the words fixed by masorah. </p>
									<p>Wooden rollers with ivory handles (590mm high). </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
